race.comment: GOLD FRONT (1) is building towards a win with placings at his last two runs, the latest effort a third over 1509m at this track (Turf) when beaten 5 lengths. Should be poised just off the lead. Will give a great sight. RANGO (8) was rewarded with his maiden success last start, scoring by one length over 1509m at this track (Turf). Looks well placed and he should be in the finish again. WOW THAT'S HOT (3) has not appeared since he finished fourth over 1609m at Lone Star Park (Dirt) on July 4. Looks a strong top-three prospect. MONEYLINE (6) looks close to a win, finishing in the placings at his last couple of runs including a second most recently over 1609m at this track (Turf) when beaten a nose. Should camp just off the leaders. One of the better hopes. Something for the Multiples: DOWN THE ISLANDS (5)
